news.title: Don't keep appeals pending for no valid reason, Chandigarh housing board officials told
news.para: As per available information, the CHB has implemented e-services in the month of February and from July 1 acceptance of physical applications has been stopped for those services that have been made available online.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to create 'repair fund' to help heritage building owners in financial distress
news.para: ​Mayor Firhad Hakim on Wednesday said all major corporates that own heritage buildings in Kolkata will have to ensure they are properly maintained.

news.title: Now, defence ministry wants to turn lease land into free-hold
news.para: People who are likely to be affected by the amendment may give their feedback, either by way of suggestions or raising objections, by July 24 (one month from the date of gazette notification issued on June 24).

news.title: Mumbai: 19 residential buildings set to make way for Sewri-Worli connector
news.para: While residents are to be moved to a project-affected people (PAP) tenement at Gomata Nagar, Worli, commercial establishments will be moved into Shirodkar Mandai at J Bhandarkar Marg, Parel.

news.title: Somany Ceramics aims at Rs 2,700 crore turnover this fiscal
news.para: The company's three plants in Haryana, Gujarat and Andhra Pradesh have a total manufacturing capacity of 75 million square metre per annum, including those of the seven subsidiaries and associate facilities, Somany Ceramics Deputy CEO Amit Sahai said.

news.title: Lucknow development body to cancel allotment of 150 houses
news.para: The action was taken after LDA vice-chairperson Indramani Tripathi sanctioned an order based on a complaint that LDA flats and houses are being used for illegal activities.

news.title: Delhi: MCD issues notices to 40,000 residents over property tax
news.para: According to officials, the move is aimed to track those who have not filed property tax for years and also to serve the purpose of updating records.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing raises Rs 500 crore from LIC via bonds
news.para: Life Insurance Corporation is said to have subscribed those bonds, rated AA (Stable) by rating company ICRA. LIC could not be contacted immediately for comments.Those are 10-year bonds that offer 9.70 percent. The proceeds will likely be used to build up the loan book.

news.title: Noida: No call yet on structural audit of seven buildings around Supertech twin towers
news.para: Arora had also said his company had delivered the society 18 years ago and cited UP-Rera rules that a builder’s liability is only for the first five years, after which it’s an RWA’s job to maintain a society.

news.title: MahaRERA dubs investor of a stalled project promoter
news.para: MahaRERA said the shareholder agreement affords the investor conclusive opportunity to "stall project completion" or "set tone and direction of the project" making it fall in the definition of ‘promoter’ under the Act.

news.title: CBI arrests businessman from Mumbai in DHFL scam case
news.para: Following the registration of the case on June 20, a team of over 50 CBI officials carried out searches on 12 premises in Mumbai belonging to the FIR-listed accused, including Sudhakar Shetty of Amaryllis Realtors and eight other builders, on June 22.

news.title: Homexchange raises funds from HDFC Capital, Oberoi Realty, Anarock
news.para: It plans to use the funds to expand its geographic presence, strengthen developer partnerships, hire talent, and further build out its technology platform.

news.title: Credit profile of most construction entities to remain resilient to input cost pressure: ICRA
news.para: The industry is grappling with input cost pressure, in the backdrop of a substantial increase in major commodity costs, particularly steel, bitumen, and cement.

news.title: Rs 940 crore land freed of squatters in 100 days, most near Noida airport
news.para: Over the past three months, anti-encroachment drives were carried out in Jhajhar, Inayatpur, Dorpur, Khandeha, Simrauthi and Dankaur and in the villages of Mathura.

news.title: DevX launches 1.5 lakh sq ft space in Noida
news.para: DevX plans to invest Rs 60 crore to double it's portfolio and have a pan-India presence by 2022 end.
